Class.Name: NSArray
Class.Description: A static ordered collection of objects.

InstanceMethods.Name: init
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly allocated array.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithArray:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly allocated array by placing in it the objects contained in a given array.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithArray:copyItems:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly allocated array using anArray as the source of data objects for the array.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithContentsOfFile:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly allocated array with the contents of the file specified by a given path.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithContentsOfURL:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly allocated array with the contents of the location specified by a given URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithObjects:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly allocated array by placing in it the objects in the argument list.

InstanceMethods.Name: initWithObjects:count:
InstanceMethods.Description: Initializes a newly allocated array to include a given number of objects from a given C array.

InstanceMethods.Name: containsObject:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether a given object is present in the array.

InstanceMethods.Name: getObjects:
InstanceMethods.Description: Copies all the objects contained in the array to aBuffer.

InstanceMethods.Name: getObjects:range:
InstanceMethods.Description: Copies references to objects contained in the array that fall within the specified range to aBuffer.

InstanceMethods.Name: objectAtIndex:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the object located at the specified index.

InstanceMethods.Name: objectAtIndexedSubscript:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the object at the specified index.

InstanceMethods.Name: objectsAtIndexes:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an array containing the objects in the array at the indexes specified by a given index set.

InstanceMethods.Name: objectEnumerator
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an enumerator object that lets you access each object in the array.

InstanceMethods.Name: reverseObjectEnumerator
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an enumerator object that lets you access each object in the array, in reverse order.

InstanceMethods.Name: indexOfObject:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the lowest index whose corresponding array value is equal to a given object.

InstanceMethods.Name: indexOfObject:inRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the lowest index within a specified range whose corresponding array value is equal to a given object .

InstanceMethods.Name: indexOfObjectIdenticalTo:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the lowest index whose corresponding array value is identical to a given object.

InstanceMethods.Name: indexOfObjectIdenticalTo:inRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the lowest index within a specified range whose corresponding array value is equal to a given object .

InstanceMethods.Name: indexOfObjectPassingTest:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the index of the first object in the array that passes a test in a given block.

InstanceMethods.Name: indexOfObjectWithOptions:passingTest:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the index of an object in the array that passes a test in a given block for a given set of enumeration options.

InstanceMethods.Name: indexOfObjectAtIndexes:options:passingTest:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the index, from a given set of indexes, of the first object in the array that passes a test in a given block for a given set of enumeration options.

InstanceMethods.Name: indexesOfObjectsPassingTest:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the indexes of objects in the array that pass a test in a given block.

InstanceMethods.Name: indexesOfObjectsWithOptions:passingTest:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the indexes of objects in the array that pass a test in a given block for a given set of enumeration options.

InstanceMethods.Name: indexesOfObjectsAtIndexes:options:passingTest:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the indexes, from a given set of indexes, of objects in the array that pass a test in a given block for a given set of enumeration options.

InstanceMethods.Name: indexOfObject:inSortedRange:options:usingComparator:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the index, within a specified range, of an object compared with elements in the array using a given NSComparator block.

InstanceMethods.Name: makeObjectsPerformSelector:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sends to each object in the array the message identified by a given selector, starting with the first object and continuing through the array to the last object.

InstanceMethods.Name: makeObjectsPerformSelector:withObject:
InstanceMethods.Description: Sends the aSelector message to each object in the array, starting with the first object and continuing through the array to the last object.

InstanceMethods.Name: enumerateObjectsUsingBlock:
InstanceMethods.Description: Executes a given block using each object in the array, starting with the first object and continuing through the array to the last object.

InstanceMethods.Name: enumerateObjectsWithOptions:usingBlock:
InstanceMethods.Description: Executes a given block using each object in the array with the specified options.

InstanceMethods.Name: enumerateObjectsAtIndexes:options:usingBlock:
InstanceMethods.Description: Executes a given block using the objects in the array at the specified indexes.

InstanceMethods.Name: firstObjectCommonWithArray:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns the first object contained in the receiving array that’s equal to an object in another given array.

InstanceMethods.Name: isEqualToArray:
InstanceMethods.Description: Compares the receiving array to another array.

InstanceMethods.Name: arrayByAddingObject:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new array that is a copy of the receiving array with a given object added to the end.

InstanceMethods.Name: arrayByAddingObjectsFromArray:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new array that is a copy of the receiving array with the objects contained in another array added to the end.

InstanceMethods.Name: filteredArrayUsingPredicate:
InstanceMethods.Description: Evaluates a given predicate against each object in the receiving array and returns a new array containing the objects for which the predicate returns true.

InstanceMethods.Name: subarrayWithRange:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new array containing the receiving array’s elements that fall within the limits specified by a given range.

InstanceMethods.Name: sortedArrayUsingFunction:context:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new array that lists the receiving array’s elements in ascending order as defined by the comparison function comparator.

InstanceMethods.Name: sortedArrayUsingFunction:context:hint:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new array that lists the receiving array’s elements in ascending order as defined by the comparison function comparator.

InstanceMethods.Name: sortedArrayUsingDescriptors:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a copy of the receiving array sorted as specified by a given array of sort descriptors.

InstanceMethods.Name: sortedArrayUsingSelector:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an array that lists the receiving array’s elements in ascending order, as determined by the comparison method specified by a given selector.

InstanceMethods.Name: sortedArrayUsingComparator:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an array that lists the receiving array’s elements in ascending order, as determined by the comparison method specified by a given NSComparator block.

InstanceMethods.Name: sortedArrayWithOptions:usingComparator:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an array that lists the receiving array’s elements in ascending order, as determined by the comparison method specified by a given NSComparator block.

InstanceMethods.Name: componentsJoinedByString:
InstanceMethods.Description: Constructs and returns an NSString object that is the result of interposing a given separator between the elements of the array.

InstanceMethods.Name: descriptionWithLocale:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a string that represents the contents of the array, formatted as a property list.

InstanceMethods.Name: descriptionWithLocale:indent:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a string that represents the contents of the array, formatted as a property list.

InstanceMethods.Name: writeToFile:atomically:
InstanceMethods.Description: Writes the contents of the array to a file at a given path.

InstanceMethods.Name: writeToURL:atomically:
InstanceMethods.Description: Writes the contents of the array to the location specified by a given URL.

InstanceMethods.Name: pathsMatchingExtensions:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an array containing all the pathname elements in the receiving array that have filename extensions from a given array.

InstanceMethods.Name: addObserver:forKeyPath:options:context:
InstanceMethods.Description: Raises an exception.

InstanceMethods.Name: removeObserver:forKeyPath:
InstanceMethods.Description: Raises an exception.

InstanceMethods.Name: removeObserver:forKeyPath:context:
InstanceMethods.Description: Raises an exception.

InstanceMethods.Name: removeObserver:fromObjectsAtIndexes:forKeyPath:context:
InstanceMethods.Description: Raises an exception.

InstanceMethods.Name: addObserver:toObjectsAtIndexes:forKeyPath:options:context:
InstanceMethods.Description: Registers an observer to receive key value observer notifications for the specified key-path relative to the objects at the indexes.

InstanceMethods.Name: removeObserver:fromObjectsAtIndexes:forKeyPath:
InstanceMethods.Description: Removes anObserver from all key value observer notifications associated with the specified keyPath relative to the array’s objects at indexes.

InstanceMethods.Name: setValue:forKey:
InstanceMethods.Description: Invokes setValue:forKey: on each of the array's items using the specified value and key.

InstanceMethods.Name: valueForKey:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns an array containing the results of invoking valueForKey: using key on each of the array's objects.

InstanceMethods.Name: shuffledArray
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new array that lists this array’s elements in a random order.

InstanceMethods.Name: shuffledArrayWithRandomSource:
InstanceMethods.Description: Returns a new array that lists this array’s elements in a random order, using the specified random source.

InstanceMethods.Name: differenceFromArray:
InstanceMethods.Description: Compares two arrays to create a difference object that represents the changes between them.

InstanceMethods.Name: differenceFromArray:withOptions:
InstanceMethods.Description: Compares two arrays, with options, to create a difference object that represents the changes between them.

InstanceMethods.Name: differenceFromArray:withOptions:usingEquivalenceTest:
InstanceMethods.Description: Compares two arrays, using the provided block and with options, to create a difference object that represents the changes between them.

InstanceMethods.Name: arrayByApplyingDifference:
InstanceMethods.Description: Creates a new array by applying a difference object to an existing array.

InstanceProperties.Name: count
InstanceProperties.Description: The number of objects in the array.

InstanceProperties.Name: firstObject
InstanceProperties.Description: The first object in the array.

InstanceProperties.Name: lastObject
InstanceProperties.Description: The last object in the array.

InstanceProperties.Name: sortedArrayHint
InstanceProperties.Description: Analyzes the array and returns a “hint” that speeds the sorting of the array when the hint is supplied to sortedArrayUsingFunction:context:hint:.

InstanceProperties.Name: description
InstanceProperties.Description: A string that represents the contents of the array, formatted as a property list.

TypeMethods.Name: array
TypeMethods.Description: Creates and returns an empty array.

TypeMethods.Name: arrayWithArray:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates and returns an array containing the objects in another given array.

TypeMethods.Name: arrayWithContentsOfFile:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates and returns an array containing the contents of the file specified by a given path.

TypeMethods.Name: arrayWithContentsOfURL:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates and returns an array containing the contents specified by a given URL.

TypeMethods.Name: arrayWithObject:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates and returns an array containing a given object.

TypeMethods.Name: arrayWithObjects:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates and returns an array containing the objects in the argument list.

TypeMethods.Name: arrayWithObjects:count:
TypeMethods.Description: Creates and returns an array that includes a given number of objects from a given C array.
